therefore the feminine of the adjective with a more loosened syllable
next to the tone, like יחשׁב־לּי in Ps 40:18), that is to say, it is
inviolable (sacrosanct), and when it is profaned, shall ever be
vindicated again in its holiness. This clause, formulated after the
manner of a prayer, is at the same time a petition that Jahve in all
time to come would be pleased to thoroughly secure the place where His
honour dwells here below against profanation.

